                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Consultation 3(A)/431: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-20T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 20, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>568. For Spaeth from Duggan. Department perceives no objection to your supporting
                    the formula and procedure suggested by the Brazilian and Venezuelan members
                    described in your 977, November 16, 4 p.m. This step would appear to be
                    consistent with more positive action, your 948 of November 8 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >5</hi>], the advisability of which the Department desires to consider
                    further. [Duggan.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
